<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?>
<dmn:definitions xmlns:dmn="https://www.omg.org/spec/DMN/20240513/MODEL/" xmlns="http://www.trisotech.com/definitions/_5fd62b57-473f-496d-9cfc-ae360c592a24" xmlns:rss="http://purl.org/rss/2.0/" xmlns:di="http://www.omg.org/spec/DMN/20180521/DI/" xmlns:trisofeed="http://trisotech.com/feed" xmlns:trisodmn="http://www.trisotech.com/2016/triso/dmn" xmlns:dmndi="https://www.omg.org/spec/DMN/20230324/DMNDI/" xmlns:dc="http://www.omg.org/spec/DMN/20180521/DC/" xmlns:triso="http://www.trisotech.com/2015/triso/modeling" xmlns:tc="http://www.omg.org/spec/DMN/20160719/testcase" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:feel="https://www.omg.org/spec/DMN/20240513/FEEL/" xmlns:drools="https://kie.org/dmn/extensions/1.0" xmlns:openapi="https://openapis.org/omg/extension/1.0" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:boxedext="https://www.trisotech.com/spec/DMN/20191111/EXT/" xmlns:i18n="http://www.omg.org/spec/BPMN/non-normative/extensions/i18n/1.0" id="_5fd62b57-473f-496d-9cfc-ae360c592a24" name="AirplanePrediction" typeLanguage="https://www.omg.org/spec/DMN/20240513/FEEL/" namespace="http://www.trisotech.com/definitions/_5fd62b57-473f-496d-9cfc-ae360c592a24">
  <dmn:description>## Overview
Use this model to assess a patient&apos;s risk of developing Deep Vein Thrombosis (DVT) during air travel and recommend a flight decision (OK to go, Modify plans, or Cancel flight).
## Inputs
- LVEF (tLVEF, number ≤100) — Left Ventricular Ejection Fraction for CHF risk.
- FlightData (tFlightData) — Contains Distance (km) and Duration (hrs).
- PatientHeight (number, ≤3m) / PatientBodyWeight (number, 0–500kg) — Used to calculate BMI.
- HasCancer, RecentSurgery, Hypercoagulable, HormoneTherapy, IsPregnant, RecentAMI (boolean) — DVT risk factors.
- EffectiveInterventionAvailable (boolean) — Whether a medical intervention can mitigate DVT risk.
## Use cases
- Pre-flight medical clearance for patients with cardiovascular conditions.
- Travel advisory for patients with known DVT risk factors.
- Insurance or airline medical screening workflows.
- Clinical decision support for flight fitness assessments.
## Do not use when
- The patient is not planning air travel.
- DVT risk is being assessed for non-travel contexts (e.g. post-surgical bed rest).
- The patient has conditions outside the scope of this model&apos;s risk factors.
## Main entry points
- FlightDecision (tFlightDecision) — Returns &quot;OK to go&quot;, &quot;Modify plans&quot;, or &quot;Cancel flight&quot;.</dmn:description>
