  <dmn:decision id="_4996f7b8-d657-4564-98dd-715c74c37d2e" name="CHFRisk">
    <dmn:description>## What it decides
Use this decision to assess the patient&apos;s Congestive Heart Failure risk level based on LVEF.
## Call when
- The patient has a known LVEF value and cardiac risk must be factored into flight DVT risk.
## Do not call when
- LVEF is unknown or cardiac history is not relevant.
## Inputs
- LVEF (tLVEF, number ≤100) — ejection fraction percentage.
## Output
- `&quot;High&quot;`: LVEF &lt; 20 (severe heart failure).
- `&quot;Moderate&quot;`: LVEF 20–44 (reduced function).
- `&quot;Low&quot;`: LVEF 45–100 (normal/preserved function).
## Examples
- LVEF 15 → `&quot;High&quot;`
- LVEF 35 → `&quot;Moderate&quot;`
- LVEF 60 → `&quot;Low&quot;`</dmn:description>
