  <dmn:decision id="_d18b383d-f28d-4ffe-bc92-e7ed1724db17" name="DVTRiskFactors">
    <dmn:description>## What it decides
Use this decision to classify the patient&apos;s personal DVT risk level based on medical history and BMI.
## Call when
- Assessing patient-specific thrombosis risk factors before flight clearance.
## Do not call when
- No patient medical data is available.
## Inputs
- HasCancer (boolean) — active cancer diagnosis (High).
- RecentSurgery (boolean) — surgery within 4–6 weeks (High).
- Hypercoagulable (boolean) — thrombophilia disorder (High).
- HormoneTherapy (boolean) — HRT or oral contraceptives (Moderate).
- IsPregnant (boolean) — current pregnancy (Moderate).
- RecentAMI (boolean) — recent heart attack (Moderate).
- CalculateBMI (number) — BMI &gt;30 is Moderate risk.
## Output
- `&quot;High&quot;`: cancer, recent surgery, or hypercoagulable state.
- `&quot;Moderate&quot;`: hormone therapy, pregnancy, recent AMI, or obesity.
- `&quot;Low&quot;`: no significant risk factors.
## Examples
- HasCancer=true → `&quot;High&quot;`
- IsPregnant=true, BMI=28 → `&quot;Moderate&quot;`
- All false, BMI=24 → `&quot;Low&quot;`</dmn:description>
